 Add Starship to your Shell
To use Starship, you need to add it to the configuration file of your shell. Here are the steps for different shells:

For Ba 
Open your .bashrc file in a text editor:

 
 
nano ~/. rc
Add the following line to the end of the file:

 
 
eval "$(starship init bash)"
Save and close the file, then reload your shell configuration:

 
 
source ~/. rc
For Z 
Open your .zshrc file in a text editor:

 
 
nano ~/.z rc
Add the following line to the end of the file:

 
 
eval "$(starship init zsh)"
Save and close the file, then reload your shell configuration:

 
 
source ~/.z rc
For Fi 
Open your config.fish file in a text editor:

 
 
nano ~/.config/fi /config.fi 
Add the following line to the end of the file:

 
 
starship init fish | source
Save and close the file, then reload your shell configuration:

 
 
source ~/.config/fi /config.fi 
